{"word":"ἀνδρόω","slug":"ἀνδρόω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἀνδρόω</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:ἀνήρ'><el>ἀνήρ</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>to rear up into manhood</i>, <b><a href='S:Anthology'>Anth.</a></b>: —<a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a> <i>to become a man, reach manhood</i>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b>in <a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a> also of a woman, <i>to be of marriageable age</i>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}